The paper focuses on studying social status and communication behavior in an evolving online social network, which falls under the scope of social network analysis and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to predict users' social status based on their behavior, which falls under the scope of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the implications of their findings for cybersecurity, which falls under the scope of cs.CYBER.
